# No Claude subagents

**Never** use the Task tool (or any subagent launcher) with a Claude model.

Banned model slugs include any `claude-*` id, for example:

- `claude-fable-5-thinking-high`
- `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-high`
- `claude-sonnet-5-thinking-high`

## Do instead

- Implement, explore, and edit **in the parent agent** (this session).
- Prefer Grep / Read / Shell / direct edits over spawning a Claude worker.
- If parallel Task agents are truly needed, use a **non-Claude** model only, and never two agents writing the same files.

## Why

Claude subagents have caused mid-edit races and API-mismatch breakages in this repo; keep ownership of files in one agent.
